   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject Two Hundred Seven THE TORMENT OF HELL Scripture: Rev 14:9-11; 21:8; Mark 9:43, 48 Hell is the portion of God s wrath</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>In Rev 14:10 cup means portion.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Because of God s love toward man, He accomplished redemption for him.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>If a man refuses to repent, he remains under God s wrath.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The totality of God s wrath is hell.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>There is fire and brimstone in hell Fire burns man.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Brimstone chokes man.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The lake of fire which burns with brimstone is unquenchable.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>There are worms that do not die in hell</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>To be bitten by mosquitoes, bugs, or fleas is already unbearable, but imagine the torment from the worms in hell which do not die with the unquenchable fire!</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>How to escape hell</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Develop this point.</S>
   </TEXT>
